Vice President Mike Pence spoke at Motor City Solutions in Taylor, Michigan, praising the automotive industry and its workers. He highlighted the Trump administration's efforts to support American workers and create jobs, including cutting red tape, unleashing American energy, and signing the largest tax cut and tax reform in American history. Pence emphasized the importance of the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and urged Congress to pass it, stating that it would level the playing field for American autoworkers and lead to more jobs and investment in the industry. He also mentioned the recent investments made by automakers in Michigan and highlighted the positive impact of the USMCA on the economy. Pence called on the audience to promote the policies that have revived the American economy and to advocate for the USMCA. He ended his remarks by expressing confidence in a prosperous future for the automotive industry and America.